metadata.description:
This <Unfavorable tanshiro 100> will be the final release of this series. 

Unfavorable Tanshiro is a p5.js generative character made by @tanshiro1986.
Everyday I draw a new factor, and post a unique Tanshiro on twitter. 

Today is the 100th day since Tanshiro's birth.
Unfavorable Tanshiro #1~#99 were released on Opensea as daily record, and this memorable #100 will be concluded, improved, and released on fx(hash).

There are 1000 unique Tashiro coming from 2,400,000 different combinations.
Some special factors are the collab with JT's artwork. 

My Twitter: https://twitter.com/tanshiro1986

metadata.name: rive #26
metadata.description:
Starting with a repeatable system of colors and/or triangles typically seen in geometric abstraction, rive employs generative art to break/split/rive those patterns–and the comfort we find in them–in slight, seemingly unintentional ways.  With each subsequent split, our comfort fades as the artwork is shredded into barely recognizable fragments of a once carefully orchestrated pattern.

Not all rivings are created equal; some are subtle and barely visible while others are acute and violent.  

What holds it together is what breaks it apart.  

created using triangles and p5js

rive
abstractment, 2022

___________________________

Functionality:
Press ‘p’ to save as a png.
Press 0-9 to render at varying degrees of quality. 0 to 9 (highest quality, ~15k x ~15k, depending on the dimensions).  The window background will change colors when completed rendering.
Press ⬆️ (arrow up) to increase pixel density by 0.5.
Press ⬇️ (arrow down) to decrease pixel density by 0.5.

metadata.name: A24Z #258
metadata.description:
Every artist and collector feels the joy of both creating and collecting. But if I could share the joy of creating with collectors. And collectors with their family and friends, what may be an additive process of joy is now perhaps exponential. Joy to the power of 26 to be exact. 

In this work I invite my friends and collectors to collaborate with me. Though not in coding, but together in a process of creating narratives and visuals. Code and story. We didn’t use github, just a simple p5.js editor to try out different programs and palettes. Pedrofe and J0rdan pick their palettes tastefully and carefully. okeoke, perhaps more of a genius than he lets on, picks his palettes blind. No hex color picker. Just straight up rhymes.  

In our discussions verbal language was forbidden. Only emojis were allowed to express our tastes and views. Each emojis put down on google doc was taken with absolutely seriousness. 

Pedro: Loves to taking his daily walks on “Magic Mushroom Mountain”

J0rdan: Wonders about “Quark Question Quiches”

Okeoke: Just get lost in “Finnegans’ Flower Fields.”

It has been a great joy to present our illustration book A24Z, 8 more than you know who. Each page expresses the alphabet with the best of our knowledge in semantics and sarcasm. Collect just 1 page, collect the alphabets that spell out your name, collect the whole A to Z. Read it to your children or loved ones. Though you might need to interpolate or extrapolate with great imagination which children all have. But most importantly, like all children, have fun!

Press 1 to save png, only for Chrome, not Safari. Preview images are compressed or broken, test capture at 300 sec.

License: CC BY-NC-ND 4.0

metadata.description:
All of us have dreams, and everyone would like to meet a fairy, a genie, a wizard, or someone else who will make our dreams come true in a snap of a finger or with the wave of a wand. metadata.name: Protein #39
metadata.description:
Exploration of noise fields.

The project is written in vanilla Javascript.

The drawing is executed at window resolution.

Press '2' to double the resolution. You can press again '2' to double once more;
Press '1' to get back at the window size.
Press 's' to save a png at the current resolution. You can also right click and 'save-as' to obtain the same result.


It uses 3 external packages, both licensed under MIT license:

* https://www.npmjs.com/package/simplex-noise
* https://www.npmjs.com/package/file-saver
* https://www.npmjs.com/package/alea

metadata.name: Gardens of delusion #104
metadata.description:
We live in a perpetual state of assertive belief, and the outside world never faults us, because we escape contradiction through a process of delusion. How reassuring it is to wander in the alleys of subjectivity and take a seat to look at these gardens we create.

Click to play the audio track.
You can zoom in/out, drag and pan.
Press « A » to toggle the autoplay mode that will change the scene every 600 frames.
Press the space bar to download a screenshot of the current frame :
- width : 4096px
- height : based on ratio
- file format : PNG

———————

Gardens of delusion by Ferdinand Dervieux, 2022
Made with threejs
